# ===========================================================================
%NAME Samples1: base test
# ===========================================================================
%DESCRIPTION
# ??????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????
Something very simple, we will just execute a query on VDP (on a view linked
to the sakila data source) and check that the results match what we are
expecting.

Note the specified results will be considered to be "ordered" by default.

Also, note the results specified in a "%RESULTS" directive with a "[data]"
qualifier are specified in CSV format, specifically adhering to the
RFC4180 de-facto standard.
# ===========================================================================
%EXECUTION[query]
{ ds:vdp }
SELECT first_name,last_name
FROM sakila_actor
WHERE first_name = 'PENELOPE'
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
%RESULTS[data]
first_name,last_name
PENELOPE,GUINESS
PENELOPE,PINKETT
PENELOPE,CRONYN
PENELOPE,MONROE
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
